getAndUpdateNetworkFee().details: Note that this function can be triggered by anyone, so that     the first trader of a new epoch can avoid incurring extra gas costs

getExpectedRate(address,address,uint256).details: Gets the expected and slippage rate for exchanging src -> dest tokenworstRate is hardcoded to be 3% lower of expectedRate

params.srcQty: Amount of src tokens in twei

returns.expectedRate: for a trade after deducting network fee.
returns.worstRate: for a trade. Calculated to be expectedRate * 97 / 100

getExpectedRateWithHintAndFee(address,ad.details: gets the expected rates when trading src -> dest token, with / without fees

params.hint: Advanced instructions for running the trade
params.platformFeeBps: Part of the trade that is allocated as fee to platform wallet. Ex: 1000 = 10%
params.srcQty: Amount of src tokens in twei

returns.rateWithAllFees: = actual rate. Rate after accounting for both network and platform fees
returns.rateWithNetworkFee: Rate after deducting network fee but excluding platform fee

params.expiryTimestamp: Timestamp for which networkFeeBps will expire,     and needs to be updated by calling kyberDao contract / set to default
params.negligibleDiffBps: Negligible rate difference (in basis pts) when searching best rate
params.networkFeeBps: Network fees to be charged (in basis pts)

listReservesForToken(address,uint256,uin.details: Allow or prevent to trade token -> eth for list of reserves      Useful for migration to new network contract      Call storage to get list of reserves supporting token -> eth

params.add: If true, then give reserve token allowance, otherwise set zero allowance
params.endIndex: end index in reserves list (can be larger)

listTokenForReserve(address,address,bool.details: Allow or prevent to trade token -> eth for a reserve

params.add: If true, then give reserve token allowance, otherwise set zero allowance

tradeWithHint(address,address,uint256,ad.details: Trade from src to dest token and sends dest token to destAddress

params.hint: Advanced instructions for running the trade
params.maxDestAmount: A limit on the amount of dest tokens in twei
params.minConversionRate: The minimal conversion rate. If actual rate is lower, trade reverts
params.srcAmount: Amount of src tokens in twei
params.trader: Address of the taker side of this trade
params.walletId: Platform wallet address for receiving fees

returns.destAmount: Amount of actual dest tokens in twei

tradeWithHintAndFee(address,address,uint.details: Trade from src to dest token and sends dest token to destAddress

params.hint: Advanced instructions for running the trade
params.maxDestAmount: A limit on the amount of dest tokens in twei
params.minConversionRate: The minimal conversion rate. If actual rate is lower, trade reverts
params.platformFeeBps: Part of the trade that is allocated as fee to platform wallet. Ex: 1000 = 10%
params.platformWallet: Platform wallet address for receiving fees
params.srcAmount: Amount of src tokens in twei
params.trader: Address of the taker side of this trade

returns.destAmount: Amount of actual dest tokens in twei

transferAdmin(address).details: Allows the current admin to set the pendingAdmin address

params.newAdmin: The address to transfer ownership to

transferAdminQuickly(address).details: Allows the current admin to set the admin in one tx. Useful initial deployment.

params.newAdmin: The address to transfer ownership to.

params.token: IERC20 The address of the token contract
